# Shared Runtime Contract
- API contract is JSON-first.
- Public API surface is versioned under `/api/v1`.
- Auth contract is Sanctum Bearer token based (client sends `Authorization: Bearer <token>`).
- Keep response payloads deterministic (stable keys, explicit fields).


# Development Scripts

Root only (orchestrator of backend + web):

```bash
npm run restore      # backend restore + web restore
npm run start        # start backend + web in parallel
npm run build:prod   # production build of web (web/dist)
```

# Production Environment
- Host: SupportHost cPanel
- URL: `https://tastespot.crointhemorning.com`
- Paths: repo `/home/crointhe/repositories/tastespot` | app `/home/crointhe/public_html/tastespot/` | docroot `/home/crointhe/public_html/tastespot/public`

# Deploy
- Target: backend API + web SPA on same host
- Trigger: push `main` (auto) or `workflow_dispatch` via `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`
- Auto-deploy paths: `backend/**`, `web/**`, `scripts/deploy.sh`, `.cpanel.yml`, `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`
- Prereq: `npm run build:prod` + commit `web/dist/`
- Secrets: `CPANEL_USER`, `CPANEL_TOKEN`
- Flow: Actions `VersionControl/update` -> `VersionControlDeployment/create` -> cPanel runs `.cpanel.yml` -> `scripts/deploy.sh`
- Verify: Actions green, `GET /api/v1/ping` ok, SPA served on production URL
- Source of truth: `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`, `.github/workflows/web-ci.yml`, `.cpanel.yml`, `scripts/deploy.sh`, `backend/DEPLOY.md`
- [backend/DEPLOY.md](../backend/DEPLOY.md) - Backend deploy details (procedural)